title: ICE: rustc panicked with GAT and type_alias_impl_trait enabled

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code ```Rust #![feature(generic_associated_types)] #![feature(type_alias_impl_trait)] pub trait Sampler { type Iter<'a, F: FnMut(&D) -> f64>: Iterator where Self: 'a; fn sample f64>(&self, pdf: F) -> Self::Iter<'_, F>; } pub struct Metropolis>(Vec, S); impl> Sampler> for Metropolis { type Iter<'a, F: FnMut(&Vec) -> f64> where S: 'a, = impl Iterator> + 'a; fn sample) -> f64>(&self, mut pdf: F) -> Self::Iter<'_, F> { || { self.1.sample(|_| 0.0); }; std::iter::empty() } } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.60.0-nightly (e7aca8959 2022-02-09) binary: rustc commit-hash: e7aca895980f25f6d2d3c48e10fd04656764d1e4 commit-date: 2022-02-09 host: aarch64-apple-darwin release: 1.60.0-nightly LLVM version: 13.0.0 ``` ### Error output ``` Compiling probs v0.3.1 (path/to/probs) thread 'rustc' panicked at 'called `Result::unwrap()` on an `Err` value: PlaceBuilder { base: Upvar { var_hir_id: HirId { owner: DefId(0:20 ~ probs[3480]::{impl#0}::sample), local_id: 2 }, closure_def_id: DefId(0:22 ~ probs[3480]::{impl#0}::sample::{closure#0}), closure_kind: Fn }, projection: [Deref, Field(field[1], S)] }', compiler/rustc_mir_build/src/build/expr/as_place.rs:303:69 ```
